<h1>Birthday Reminders</h1>
<p>Get push notifications when registered people's birthdays are approaching.</p>

<h2>Setting Up Reminders</h2>
<ol>
  <li>Go to Settings.</li>
  <li>Turn on <strong>Birthday Reminders</strong>.</li>
  <li>Set the notification time (e.g., 9:00 AM).</li>
  <li>Choose the reminder range.</li>
</ol>

<h2>Reminder Range</h2>
<p>You can receive reminders at the following intervals:</p>
<ul>
  <li><strong>D-30</strong> — 30 days before the birthday</li>
  <li><strong>D-7</strong> — 7 days before</li>
  <li><strong>D-1</strong> — The day before</li>
  <li><strong>D-day</strong> — On the birthday</li>
</ul>
<p>Multiple ranges can be selected at the same time.</p>

<h2>Checking Upcoming Birthdays</h2>
<p>Tap the birthday reminder button at the top of the main screen to see a list of upcoming birthdays.</p>

<h2>Notes</h2>
<ul>
  <li>Reminders will arrive at the set time even after closing the app.</li>
  <li>Lunar birthdays are automatically converted to solar dates for accurate reminders.</li>
</ul>

<h2>Troubleshooting</h2>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Android 13+</strong> — You must grant notification permission after installing. Check Settings → Apps → AgeMap → Notifications.</li>
  <li><strong>Battery optimization</strong> — Some devices may block notifications due to battery optimization. Go to Settings → Battery → AgeMap and set to "Unrestricted".</li>
</ul>
